The culture of pride in "making direct" still exists, he said, adding that modern technology and increasing pressure on students make this a growing problem.
To ensure that we sleep enough and with quality should be a "secret weapon" of students to combat stress, exhaustion and anxiety, he said, and even to avoid getting fat, because sleep deprivation puts the brain into hunger mode, making them constantly hungry.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old Californian student of physical and chemical biology, helped Professor Czeisler design the course after having attended one of his classes last year in the first year at Harvard.
